  <item rdf:about="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/000624.php">
    <title>Simply Awesome!</title>
    <description>I&apos;m back from Canada and my head is still woozy from all those impressions that hammered down on me during the last days. FITC was definitely the best conference ever I&apos;ve been to. Shawn Pucknell and his team have put so much love and effort into every little detail of this event - it just blew me away. I&apos;m very proud that I could be part of this. Thank you to everyone who attended my session - I will try to publish the lecture notes and the files for Flash live sound analysis and MIDI control next week. Of course</description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I'm back from Canada and my head is still woozy from all those impressions that hammered down on me during the last days. <a href="http://www.fitc.ca">FITC</a> was definitely the best conference ever I've been to. Shawn Pucknell and his team have put so much love and effort into every little detail of this event - it just blew me away. I'm very proud that I could be part of this. Thank you to everyone who attended my session - I will try to publish the lecture notes and the files for Flash live sound analysis and MIDI control next week.</p>

<p>Of course the most important part about any conference is the attendants and I was really lucky to have had the chance to have fun and talk with such a lot of wonderful people: <a href="http://www.galaxygoo.org/blogs/index.html">Kristin</a>, <a href="http://www.moock.org">Colin</a>, <a href="http://www.flashant.org">Aral</a>, <a href="http://www.gskinner.com/blog/">Grant and Bobi</a>, <a href="http://www.quantumwave.com/flash/">Dave</a>, <a href="http://www.rewindlife.com/">Chafic</a>, <a href="http://www.ifbin.com">Ted</a>, <a href="http://www.flight404.com/version8/index.html">Robert</a>, <a href="http://www.robertpenner.com">Robert</a>, <a href="http://www.tomontheweb.ca/">Tom</a>, <a href="http://www.newyyz.com">Kevin</a>, <a href="http://www.angryalien.com">Jen</a>, <a href="http://www.reflektions.com/miniml/default.asp">Paul</a>, <a href="http://www.natzke.com">Erik</a>, <a href="http://benfry.com/">Ben</a>, <a href="http://www.crashmedia.com">Craig</a>, <a href="http://www.waxpraxis.org/">Branden</A>, <a href="http://TheUnseenVideo.com">Daniel</a>, <a href="http://www.aaronphelan.com/">Aaron</a>, <a href="http://blogs.adobe.com/jnack/">John</a>, <a href="http://www.darronschall.com">Darron</a>, <a href="http://www.lordalex.org/">Lord Alex</a>, <a href="http://www.margotknight.com">Margot</a>, <a href="http://www.bit-101.com">Keith</a>, <a href="http://blogs.adobe.com/skilisky/">Steve</a>, <a href="http://www.themakers.com">Snow and Robert</a>, <a href="http://www.sagmeister.com">Stefan</a>, <a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/md/">Mike</a> and <a href="http://weblogs.macromedia.com/mesh/">Mike</A>. Oh and I'm sure that I forgot someone here.</p>

<p>A last tip: if you happen to be in Toronto and you read "Kids & Explosions" on a flyer someday - you have to go to that party. Josh is absolutely awesome and I really hope to get the chance to see (or rather hear) him again.</p>]]></content:encoded>
