  <item rdf:about="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/000620.php">
    <title>Flash 8: Measuring Line Widths of TextFields</title>
    <description>While ActionScript 3.0 comes with the TextLineMetrics Class that allows you to get all kinds of information about a text selection, with Flash 8 and below you have to go all the way on your feet if you want to know the width or position of a line of text within a textfield. Before Flash 8 the only way I know of to accomplish this was to split the whole text into single words and add up their widths. But Flash 8 offers a new way to do this which works by using a BitmapData object together with the rarely</description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>While ActionScript 3.0 comes with the <a href="http://livedocs.macromedia.com/labs/1/flex/langref/flash/text/TextLineMetrics.html">TextLineMetrics Class</a> that allows you to get all kinds of information about a text selection, with Flash 8 and below you have to go all the way on your feet if you want to know the width or position of a line of text within a textfield. </p>

<p>Before Flash 8 the only way I know of to accomplish this was to <a href="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/000526.php">split the whole text into single words</a> and add up their widths. But Flash 8 offers a new way to do this which works by using a BitmapData object together with the rarely used getColorBoundsRect() method. Check out the code and a demo here:</p>]]></content:encoded>
