  <item rdf:about="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/000617.php">
    <title>Flash BitmapExporter in Action</title>
    <description>I just got notice that my Flash 8 BitmapExporter class is currently being used in a real world assignment: on spamrecycling.com it allows users to save images created from the innards of creatively recycled spam emails. To try it yourself, all you have to do is to forward a spam mail you&apos;ve received to spam@spamrecycling.com. Shortly after you will receive a reply email containing a link to your personal spam recycling tool which allows you to get artistic with the garbage mail. When you are satisfied with the outcome you can take a screenshot and have it sent to your</description>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I just got notice that my <a href="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/000572.php">Flash 8 BitmapExporter class</a> is currently being used in a real world assignment:  on <a href="http://www.spamrecycling.com">spamrecycling.com</a> it allows users to save images created from the innards of creatively recycled spam emails. To try it yourself, all you have to do is to forward a spam mail you've received to <a href="mailto:spam@spamrecycling.com">spam@spamrecycling.com</a>.  Shortly after you will receive a reply email containing a link to your personal spam recycling tool which allows you to get artistic with the garbage mail. When you are satisfied with the outcome you can take a screenshot and have it sent to your email adress. </p>

<p>The task of the BitmapExporter in this project is to compress and send <a href="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/recycledImage.php" onclick="window.open('http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/recycledImage.php','popup','width=1024,height=768,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false">fullscreen images like this</a> to the server - for more details how this works and why this is more difficult than it might appear check out <a href="http://www.quasimondo.com/archives/000572.php">my original posting and the comments there</a>.</p>]]></content:encoded>
